<item>
            <title>[LU-4150] sanity test_133e: Bad write_bytes sum, expected 1376256, got 0</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4150</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for sarah &amp;lt;sarah@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/2a999af6-3e0a-11e3-83f5-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/2a999af6-3e0a-11e3-83f5-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_133e failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bad write_bytes sum, expected 1376256, got 0&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After rolling upgrade all servers and clients from 2.4.1 to 2.5, run sanity test, hit this error&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test log shows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity test 133e: Verifying OST {read,write}_bytes nid stats =================== 23:05:37 (1382767537)
42+0 records in
42+0 records out
1376256 bytes (1.4 MB) copied, 0.014401 s, 95.6 MB/s
 sanity test_133e: @@@@@@ FAIL: Bad write_bytes sum, expected 1376256, got 0 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment>before upgrade&lt;br/&gt;
server and client: 2.4.1 RHEL6 ldiskfs&lt;br/&gt;
after upgrade&lt;br/&gt;
server and client: 2.5 build #2 RHEL6 ldiskfs</environment>
